{"lemma":"سَيْفِ","slug":"سَيْفِ","root":"س.#.ف","root_slug":"س-_-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/س-_-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21446","n21447"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D9%81%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sword, sabre, foil, rapier, scimitar"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"coast"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"riverbank"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shore"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Related to Ancient Greek ξίφος (xíphos); either a loan, or from a common original source.\nThe same word is probably preserved in Egyptian zft, Coptic ⲥⲏϥⲉ (sēfe).\nDümichen (1867) suggested an Old Semitic saïf or sêf, Myres (1930) a possible Libyan or \"Sea Peoples\" word.\nThe root س ي ف (s y f) is denominal.\nCompare Hebrew סַיִף (sáyif)."},"ipa":["/sajf/","/seːf/","/siːf/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21446","headword_ar":"سَيْفٌ","root":"syf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sword;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, PS, &c.;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain thing with which one smites;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"its names exceed a thousand: (K: in which it is added that its author has mentioned these names in [his book entitled]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~awoDu Almasoluwfu","text_ar":"الرَّوْضُ المَسْلُوفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [for the names of particular parts thereof, see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbN","text_ar":"ذُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyaAfN","text_ar":"اَسْيَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyufN","text_ar":"اَسْيُفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M, O, K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suyuwfN","text_ar":"سُيُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, Msb, K) and [quasi-pl. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoyafapN","text_ar":"مَسْيَفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyaxapN","text_ar":"مَشْيَخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyfapN","text_ar":"مَسِيفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$iyxapN","text_ar":"مَشِيخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (CK.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayofu Aljab~aAri","text_ar":"سَيْفُ الجَبَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sword of Orion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the three stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"η, θ, κ,","text_ar":"η, θ, κ,","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath the girdle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljb~Ar","text_ar":"الجبّار"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a sloping direction, near together, disposed in a row."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw.) ―         -b2-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain fish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayof","text_ar":"سَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sword"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Ibn-'Abbád, O;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyfN","text_ar":"سِيفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiyb","text_ar":"سَبِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) [i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair of the tail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a horse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayofu AlguraAbi","text_ar":"سَيْفُ الغُرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~alabuwvu","text_ar":"الدَّلَبُوثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant, the stem"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and leaves of which are exactly like those of the saffron, and the bulb of which is enclosed in a covering of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fibres of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyf","text_ar":"لِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AHn;) so called because"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its leaves are slender at the extremity like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayof","text_ar":"سَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sword"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AHn, K.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo A^asoyaAfN","text_ar":"هُمْ اَسْيَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are swords"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHozaAbN","text_ar":"اَحْزَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they are bodies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parties, of men prepared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ready, for fighting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Ibn-'Abbád, O, K.) ―         -b6-  And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona fak~ayohi sayofN SaArimN","text_ar":"بَيْنَ فَكَّيْهِ سَيْفٌ صَارِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between his two jaws is a sharp tongue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cleaving sword"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","O","Msb","K","Lh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n21447","headword_ar":"سِيفٌ","root":"syf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shore"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAHil","text_ar":"سَاحِل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sea"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a great river:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, Mgh, Msb, K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAHil","text_ar":"سَاحِل"},{"kind":"text","text":") of a valley: or [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"margin"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the shore of a sea or of a great river; for it is added,] every"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAHil","text_ar":"سَاحِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"has a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyf","text_ar":"سِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~iyfu","text_ar":"السِّيفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied only to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyf","text_ar":"سِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or sea-shore, or seaboard,] of 'Omán: (K:) [if otherwise applied,] its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyaAfN","text_ar":"اَسْيَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo A^aholu A^asoyaAf K waA^aroyaAfK","text_ar":"هُمْ اَهْلُ اَسْيَاف ٍ وَاَرْيَافٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are people of the shores of the sea"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a great river, and of the tracts of towns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages, and cultivated lands"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that adheres to the lower parts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roots, of palm-branches, like"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fibres called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyf","text_ar":"لِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but not the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyf","text_ar":"لِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S: in which is added, “ this I have taken from a book, without having heard it: ”) or the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fibrous substance called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyf","text_ar":"لِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyf","text_ar":"لِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adhering to the lower parts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roots, of palm-branches, which is the worst sort thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lyf","text_ar":"ليف"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the harshest, and coarsest."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyfN","text_ar":"شِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayofN","text_ar":"سَيْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","M","O","Mgh","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}